Anthony Siming Chen was born in Taiyuan, China. He earned his B.Eng. (2015) in Transportation Engineering at [Central South University](https://en.csu.edu.cn/) as a member of Shenghua Honors College under a 
National Talent Program. During my undergraduate studies, he spent a one-year industrial placement at [CRRC](https://www.crrcgc.cc/en/) in China. After relocating to the United Kingdom, he obtained his M.Sc. in Advanced Mechanical Engineering (2016) and Ph.D. in Mechanical Engineering (2022) from the [University of Bristol](https://www.bristol.ac.uk/), where he conducted research within the [Dynamics and Control Research Group (DCRG)](https://www.bristol.ac.uk/engineering/research/dynamicscontrol/). I have held research and visiting positions with [The University of Manchester](https://www.manchester.ac.uk), the [Georgia Institute of Technology](https://www.gatech.edu/), the [Institute for Advanced Automotive Propulsion Systems (IAAPS)](https://iaaps.co.uk/) at the [University of Bath](https://www.bath.ac.uk/).

He currently serves as an Assistant Professor at Aerospace Engineering, Department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering at the University of Nottingham. He holds secondary appointments in the Department of Mechanical, Materials and Manufacturing Engineering (M3) and the School of Computer Science. His expertise is in control theory, reinforcement learning, and robotics.

He am an IEEE Member of the [Control Systems Society (CSS)](https://www.ieeecss.org/) and the [Robotics and Automation Society (RAS)](https://www.ieee-ras.org/). He is a member of the IEEE CSS Technical Committee of Quantum Computing, Systems and Control, IEEE RAS Technical Committee on Robot Learning, IEEE RAS Technical Committee on Robotic Hands. he regularly review for leading journals and conferences in Control and Robotics, including IEEE TAC, Automatica, IEEE TCST, IEEE CDC, IEEE L-CSS, IEEE RA-L, IEEE T-RO, IROS, and ICRA.

